v0.1 -- slightly more exciting
==============================
- separate lifestyle name and city name and display both in the link
- new lifestyle button switches to a two-input form
- counts of people who've lived in each lifestyle using calculated field
- sort lifestyles by city name
- tips -> inventory
- inventory is saved on the server side, by user id


v0.2 -- first cut of the d3.js map
==================================
- three tabs:  game, inventory, map
- d3.js
- map loads all activities and builds better_than/worse_than edges


v0.3 -- less embarassing code
=============================
- yield takes prompt and options and returns object with many attributes
- firebase setters are factored out into their own database library


v0.4 -- can replace sandbar
===========================
